						<summary>

						<p>West wall of the <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of the Brahmapurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription may be assigned on palaeographical grounds to the 14th century.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record the fixation of taxes on loom <hi rend="italic">(taṟik-kaḍamai), vāśaival-āyam</hi> and <hi rend="italic">ūr-viniyōgam</hi> evidently payable to the temple by those who had settled in the various streets at Vaḻugūr.</p>						

						<p>An incomplete record found below this contains some of the epithets of the Vijayanagara king.</p>						

						</summary>
